The threat of nuclear
terrorism has been quelled.

59:06.918 --> 59:09.921
We are in contact with
the Albanian premier...

59:09.963 --> 59:11.423
...who assures me and...

59:11.465 --> 59:13.717
...this government
credits his assurances...

59:13.759 --> 59:16.261
...that his country
does not wish us ill.

59:16.303 --> 59:17.554
Know any Latin?

59:17.596 --> 59:19.139
I, Claudius. That's what I know.

59:19.181 --> 59:22.642
I need a Latin motto for the patch.

59:22.684 --> 59:24.352
The 303 patch.

59:24.394 --> 59:28.106
...by a designation number, 303.

59:28.148 --> 59:32.319
A member of the group was left
behind, what were then, enemy lines.

59:32.360 --> 59:37.073
And I can only say to those
family members of Group 303...

59:37.115 --> 59:39.367
...whose members are,
I know as I speak...

59:39.409 --> 59:40.786
...gathering to comfort you.

59:40.827 --> 59:42.579
To the parents of the missing man...

59:42.621 --> 59:45.123
...I can only say no
effort will be spared...

59:45.165 --> 59:48.752
...to find this brave
man and bring him home.

59:48.794 --> 59:52.297
We've just received this photograph
of Schumann in captivity...

59:52.339 --> 59:55.592
...held by a dissident group
of Albanian terrorists.

59:55.634 --> 59:58.637
Now, I don't know how many of you
are familiar with Morse code...

59:58.678 --> 01:00:02.891
...but could you bring the
camera closer and here, please?

01:00:02.933 --> 01:00:05.644
You'll see his sweater is worn.

01:00:05.685 --> 01:00:07.145
It has been unraveled in places.

01:00:07.187 --> 01:00:09.898
And those places form dashes and dots...

01:00:09.940 --> 01:00:14.820
...and those dots spell out
a message in Morse code.

01:00:14.861 --> 01:00:18.406
That message is, "Courage, Mom."

01:00:18.448 --> 01:00:20.033
"Courage, Mom."

01:00:20.075 --> 01:00:23.662
He got the message
through. "Courage, Mom."

01:00:23.703 --> 01:00:25.455
Not bad for government work.

01:00:25.497 --> 01:00:27.165
Having a good time?

01:00:27.207 --> 01:00:29.459
Haven't had this much fun since live TV.

01:00:29.501 --> 01:00:32.170
To the men and women of Unit 303...

01:00:32.212 --> 01:00:34.631
...to my fellow citizens,
I say, "Courage, Mom."

01:00:34.673 --> 01:00:38.635
I have informed the Albanian
government that we will not rest...

01:00:38.677 --> 01:00:40.554
...until the safe return
of Sergeant Schumann.

01:00:40.595 --> 01:00:44.683
I'm told his unit mates gave
him the nickname "Old Shoe."

01:00:44.724 --> 01:00:48.854
Wasn't there a folk
song called "Old Shoe?"

01:00:48.895 --> 01:00:51.940
Do you remember that? Something like...

01:00:51.982 --> 01:00:56.111
I don't know. I can vaguely remember it.

01:00:56.152 --> 01:00:57.571
Do you know what I'm talking about?

01:00:57.612 --> 01:00:59.531
"Old Shoe."

01:00:59.573 --> 01:01:01.241
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

01:01:01.283 --> 01:01:03.368
Good night and God bless.

01:01:03.410 --> 01:01:08.081
Trump that, Senator Neal, you
Howdy-Doody-looking vontz.

01:01:08.123 --> 01:01:10.667
As we reported earlier, U.S.
Serviceman Willie Schumann...

01:01:10.709 --> 01:01:12.544
...remains missing behind enemy lines...

01:01:12.586 --> 01:01:15.213
It's all thinking ahead.

01:01:15.255 --> 01:01:16.756
That's what producing is.

01:01:16.798 --> 01:01:19.718
- It's like being a plumber.
- Yes. It's like being a plumber.

01:01:19.759 --> 01:01:22.387
Do your job right, nobody should notice.

01:01:22.429 --> 01:01:25.348
When you fuck up, everything
gets full of shit.

01:01:25.390 --> 01:01:27.392
...symbol of the military team...

01:01:27.434 --> 01:01:30.061
...Sergeant William
Schumann, the "Old Shoe."

01:01:30.103 --> 01:01:32.898
What do you say, we line up the
president for the Peace Prize?

01:01:32.939 --> 01:01:34.733
Our job ends on election day.

01:01:34.774 --> 01:01:38.069
Yes. But, come on.

01:01:38.111 --> 01:01:39.738
Just for the symmetry of the thing?

01:01:39.779 --> 01:01:40.739
That's right.

01:01:40.780 --> 01:01:42.741
If Kissinger can win the Peace Prize...

01:01:42.782 --> 01:01:46.119
...I wouldn't be surprised to wake up
and find out I'd won the Preakness.

01:01:46.161 --> 01:01:49.789
Well, yes, but our guy did bring peace.

01:01:49.831 --> 01:01:51.249
Yeah, but there wasn't a war.

01:01:51.291 --> 01:01:55.754
All the greater accomplishment.

01:02:10.977 --> 01:02:13.438
Where's the money...

01:02:13.480 --> 01:02:16.441
Where's the tie-in with
throwing away the old shoes?

01:02:16.483 --> 01:02:18.068
Who steps up and pays you for that?

01:02:18.109 --> 01:02:20.320
You throw away the shoes.
What are you gonna do?

01:02:20.362 --> 01:02:21.821
Buy new ones.

01:02:21.863 --> 01:02:24.115
We have some powerful new friends...

01:02:24.157 --> 01:02:27.160
...at the International
Association of Shoe Manufacturers.

01:02:27.202 --> 01:02:28.828
See. You guys sure get around.

01:02:28.870 --> 01:02:30.956
Fad King is my hero. Want to go first?

01:02:30.997 --> 01:02:33.416
Sure.

01:02:35.377 --> 01:02:38.672
History, Connie.

01:02:39.130 --> 01:02:40.840
Those are ratty shoes.

01:02:40.882 --> 01:02:42.884
Yeah, that's why we're
flinging them away.

01:02:42.926 --> 01:02:47.389
You want to try some? Go ahead.

01:02:47.555 --> 01:02:49.474
Here. Do it again.

01:02:49.516 --> 01:02:53.269
Go ahead. Have a ball.

01:02:54.771 --> 01:02:57.983
Ok. Watch this.

01:03:00.068 --> 01:03:04.072
Go on, tell your friends.

01:03:04.489 --> 01:03:06.241
Well. This is interesting.

01:03:06.282 --> 01:03:10.495
I have just been handed this.
Something just discovered.

01:03:10.537 --> 01:03:13.832
A 1930s recording, part of
the folk song collection...

01:03:13.873 --> 01:03:15.500
...of the Library of Congress...

01:03:15.542 --> 01:03:18.753
...and a fitting song, if
I may say so, about Shoe.

01:03:18.795 --> 01:03:20.630
You know Schumann is
the military soldier...

01:03:20.672 --> 01:03:25.885
...who's been left behind enemy lines...

01:03:31.349 --> 01:03:33.018
Jim, can I get a word with you, please?

01:03:33.059 --> 01:03:36.730
Would you like to comment
the situation on Albania?

01:03:36.771 --> 01:03:39.149
Yes, there is one thing I'd like to say.

01:03:39.190 --> 01:03:43.236
This is to the Albanians that
have this man in custody.

01:03:43.278 --> 01:03:49.701
I mean this from the bottom of
my heart as one of your race.

01:03:49.743 --> 01:03:54.873
I didn't know Jim Belushi was Albanian.

01:03:57.959 --> 01:04:03.381
The search for Willie
Schumann continues...

01:04:29.783 --> 01:04:32.577
Tell Grace, as soon as we
land, I want a reflexologist.

01:04:32.619 --> 01:04:33.536
Male or female?

01:04:33.578 --> 01:04:35.205
- The Polish...
- The White House wants to know about...

01:04:35.246 --> 01:04:36.539
...the Congressional Medal of Honor.

01:04:36.581 --> 01:04:38.083
- What about it?
- For Schumann.

01:04:38.124 --> 01:04:40.752
Wait a minute, wait.
We got 86% in favor.

01:04:40.794 --> 01:04:44.047
We bring him back tomorrow,
charts go up, they don't go down.

01:04:44.089 --> 01:04:45.799
I don't want to tell them
how to do their business...

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:47.550
...but why don't they do
it after the election?

01:04:47.592 --> 01:04:49.511
Makes more sense, and
it'll help them more.

01:04:49.552 --> 01:04:51.554
When are you bringing
him back? Schumann?

01:04:51.596 --> 01:04:53.556
King, show him the thing.

01:04:53.598 --> 01:04:56.351
- It's not done yet. I don't wanna show him.
- Show it to him.

01:04:56.392 --> 01:04:59.104
Talk about enlarging the
market. Tell him, Faye.

01:04:59.145 --> 01:05:02.774
Here it is. Artist's
rendering of the memorial.

01:05:02.816 --> 01:05:04.067
The memorial?

01:05:04.109 --> 01:05:06.611
That's the memorial of the fallen.

01:05:06.653 --> 01:05:08.321
Of the Albanian campaign.

01:05:08.363 --> 01:05:10.115
- Lovely.
- It's better than lovely.

01:05:10.156 --> 01:05:12.242
This guy made a deal
with Governor Kneehigh...

01:05:12.283 --> 01:05:13.910
- Senator Leahy.
- Right.

01:05:13.952 --> 01:05:16.454
Connie, you have to see how much
granite you have to put in this thing.

01:05:16.496 --> 01:05:18.289
We got a site picked out and everything.

01:05:18.331 --> 01:05:20.458
And, the beauty part is...

01:05:20.500 --> 01:05:22.293
...guess who retains the
merchandising rights.

01:05:22.335 --> 01:05:24.129
- Show him the clock?
- Show him.

01:05:24.170 --> 01:05:26.089
Got it as a clock.

01:05:26.131 --> 01:05:27.674
Lovely.

01:05:27.715 --> 01:05:29.843
- We gotta get going.
- When's Schumann coming back?

01:05:29.884 --> 01:05:30.677
Getting him right now.

01:05:30.718 --> 01:05:33.513
- I need his neck size.
- You gotta get his neck size.

01:05:33.555 --> 01:05:34.806
I think it may be about 17 1/2.

01:05:34.848 --> 01:05:37.642
You know, 17 1/2, thinking
is not good enough.

01:05:37.684 --> 01:05:39.727
I'm an artist, not a factory worker.

01:05:39.769 --> 01:05:42.147
What did he eat behind enemy
lines when he's trapped?

01:05:42.188 --> 01:05:43.690
Birds, snakes.

01:05:43.731 --> 01:05:46.484
Bullshit. He ate tiny
cheeseburgers in tin foil.

01:05:46.526 --> 01:05:47.986
Pull a string, they heat themselves, ok?

01:05:48.027 --> 01:05:49.863
We call Burger King, Johnny Rockets.

01:05:49.904 --> 01:05:52.282
We get the Shoe Burger with
cheese and 303 sauce...

01:05:52.323 --> 01:05:54.742
"Behind enemy lines or anytime."

01:05:54.784 --> 01:05:56.077
- Good.
- Good? That's good.

01:05:56.119 --> 01:05:56.953
That's the slogan.

01:05:56.995 --> 01:05:59.664
And I got the copyright on
the Albanian kitten thing.

01:05:59.706 --> 01:06:01.749
I'm gonna call Nike, get Rodman
to dye his hair leopard skin.

01:06:01.791 --> 01:06:06.838
We'll have a sneaker... "Air Leopard."

01:06:07.380 --> 01:06:09.549
...a high school basketball
game last night...

01:06:09.591 --> 01:06:11.926
...between Montgomery
Bell and Blair Park.

01:06:11.968 --> 01:06:13.428
Students, during the game...

01:06:13.469 --> 01:06:16.139
...in spontaneous moment
of sheer patriotism...

01:06:16.181 --> 01:06:19.517
...threw their tennis shoes on
the court by the hundreds...

01:06:19.559 --> 01:06:21.102
...just for the Old Shoe.

01:06:21.144 --> 01:06:23.855
Bring him back. William
Schumann, soldier...

01:06:23.897 --> 01:06:25.732
There's no business like it.

01:06:25.773 --> 01:06:28.443
Demonstrations are springing
up all over the country...

01:06:28.484 --> 01:06:31.487
...as American people continue
to show their patriotism.

01:06:31.529 --> 01:06:34.449
You ought to get them to run
that inaugural speech by me.

01:06:34.490 --> 01:06:36.534
Inaugural speech? I don't know.

01:06:36.576 --> 01:06:39.412
The White House staff gonna be
jealous by given up that one.

01:06:39.454 --> 01:06:43.082
Come on, Connie. Let me
close out the thing in style.

01:06:43.124 --> 01:06:45.251
I've come to feel it's my thing.

01:06:45.293 --> 01:06:49.130
You take a job, you take a job, and
many times, it's just a job, you know.

01:06:49.172 --> 01:06:50.673
And then... You know what I mean?

01:06:50.715 --> 01:06:52.217
Hell of a ride, Stanley. Hell of a ride.

01:06:52.258 --> 01:06:53.676
Isn't it? Isn't it?

01:06:53.718 --> 01:06:55.386
You know, you take the
bitter with the sweet...

01:06:55.428 --> 01:06:57.055
...or the sweet with the bitter.

01:06:57.096 --> 01:07:00.934
What's that expression?

01:07:01.684 --> 01:07:05.396
...feeling good about the economy.

01:07:05.438 --> 01:07:07.065
That's why we're voting
for the president, Ed.

01:07:07.106 --> 01:07:08.775
What do you think?

01:07:08.816 --> 01:07:12.737
Well, Bob, my mind wasn't
100% made up, but now it is.

01:07:12.779 --> 01:07:18.368
I say, don't go changing
horses in midstream.

01:07:18.493 --> 01:07:19.953
Absolutely.

01:07:19.994 --> 01:07:22.622
Who needs surprises these days?

01:07:22.664 --> 01:07:24.582
For an economy you can rely on...

01:07:24.624 --> 01:07:27.627
Fucking amateurs.

01:07:27.669 --> 01:07:31.547
Pity of it is, two more days,
and we bring it all back home.

01:07:31.589 --> 01:07:33.132
Knock wood.

01:07:33.174 --> 01:07:35.426
And who's gonna know?

01:07:35.468 --> 01:07:38.763
Who's gonna know what we did?

01:07:38.805 --> 01:07:40.348
Pride of a job well done, Stan.

01:07:40.390 --> 01:07:45.228
It's the pride of a job well
done, but it's more that, Stanley.

01:07:45.270 --> 01:07:49.023
It's the gratitude of your
party and your president, right?

01:07:49.065 --> 01:07:53.820
- Is that the thing?
- Indeed it is. Indeed it is.

01:07:53.861 --> 01:07:57.282
Dean City, Oklahoma.
Army special programs.

01:07:57.323 --> 01:07:58.700
Tell 'em to bring Schumann to the plane.

01:07:58.741 --> 01:08:01.244
We'll bring him back and
stash him in the hospital.

